00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:04,606
and other items like bearer bonds.

246
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:08,402
It was about two billion won in total.

247
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:11,155
Today, I think it'd be worth
tens of billions of won.

248
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:15,743
It was absurd
and truly beyond anyone's imagination.

249
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:18,620
Where would they have gotten
that money from?

250
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:22,791
He embezzled it from the residents.

251
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:28,380
How many people
would you say were kept in there?

252
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:33,260
As of 1986, there were about 3,200 people.

253
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,261
DETAINEE STATUS

254
00:17:37,514 --> 00:17:41,101
At its peak,
up to 4,300 people were held there.

255
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:46,106
PARK MIN-SEONG
FORMER BUSAN CITY COUNCIL MEMBER

256
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:49,109
Considering the facility operated
from 1975 to 1987…

257
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:55,115
we estimate it held
about 38,000 people in total.

258
00:17:56,283 --> 00:17:57,493
TOTAL NUMBER OF DETAINEES
38,000

259
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,578
It was probably for money.

260
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:04,208
Their funding was based on
the number of people they held.

261
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:08,587
The more people they brought in,
the more government subsidies they got.

262
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:12,549
The more, the better.
They wanted as many as possible.

263
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:17,721
I believe they received
up to two billion won…

264
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:19,139
1.7 BILLION IN '85

265
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:22,226
…in subsidies from the Korean government.

266
00:18:22,309 --> 00:18:23,185
2.1 BILLION IN '86

267
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,813
They refused to cooperate with the police…

268
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,815
…Orders of Merit and Medals of Honor.

269
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:30,859
The Brothers' Home
must be shut down immediately.

270
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:35,697
He was arrested.

271
00:18:36,573 --> 00:18:39,368
Park In-geun was arrested
in December of '86.

272
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:46,416
I thought, "Wow, finally,
the Brothers' Home is being shut down."

273
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:52,548
"That motherfucker Park In-geun.
He'd be put away for good, wouldn't he?"

274
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:56,927
The Ulsan branch of Busan Office
requested a 15-year prison sentence

275
00:18:57,010 --> 00:19:01,181
and a fine of 681.78 million won
for the defendant, Director Park In-geun.

276
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:03,809
Prosecutors stated
they were seeking a heavy sentence,

277
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:07,980
as Park's embezzlement
of government subsidies was unacceptable

278
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:09,857
in a welfare-based society.

279
00:19:17,447 --> 00:19:21,493
JUNE 30, 1987
BROTHERS' HOME SHUTS DOWN

280
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:30,169
I was released
when the Brothers' Home shut down.

281
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,591
My family was ruined.

282
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,677
We were struggling badly.

283
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:45,267
They'd been traveling all over the country
looking for us instead of working

284
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:47,728
and ended up spending all their money.

285
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,274
My mom said she tried to find me

286
00:19:52,774 --> 00:19:57,070
by searching every single orphanage
across Korea.

287
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:00,824
As for my father,

288
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:02,618
he died of illness

289
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:05,204
after I was gone.

290
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:09,124
After that, the family fell into decline.

291
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:14,963
The entire family was shattered.

292
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:22,179
Things only got harder after I got out.

293
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:26,892
It was hard
because I couldn't live a normal life.

294
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:34,358
There was nothing… I could do.
Nothing at all.

295
00:20:35,317 --> 00:20:37,986
The hostess bar was the only place
that welcomed me.

296
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:40,322
Because I was young.

297
00:20:40,989 --> 00:20:43,367
It was humiliating,
and I didn't want to work there.

298
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:46,119
But I had no choice.

299
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:49,456
Getting out didn't end the misery.

300
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:51,959
I went to prison too.

301
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,337
I lived like a thug for a bit,

302
00:20:56,129 --> 00:20:58,715
eventually ending up in Busan prison.

303
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:19,653
I tried to take my own life

304
00:21:19,736 --> 00:21:22,906
three or four times at home.

305
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:29,121
For me, the pain of living

306
00:21:29,204 --> 00:21:31,373
was too much to bear.

307
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:35,877
I thought it'd be better to just die
and not have to exist anymore.

308
00:21:40,757 --> 00:21:45,429
I found out my little brother went through
the same things I did in there.

309
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:52,102
He attempted suicide a few times too.
He slit his wrist.

310
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:57,733
Eventually, on October 9, 2009,

311
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:00,527
I got a call from my nephew.

312
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:09,077
He was crying, saying,
"Uncle, Dad's trying to kill himself."

313
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:18,420
CHOI JAE-U

314
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,885
I felt deeply guilty.

315
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:30,349
I just…

316
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,396
miss my brother so much.

317
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:49,910
BROTHERS' HOME SHUTS DOWN
1987

318
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:53,872
ENCOUNTER WITH PARK IN-GEUN
1999

319
00:22:55,832 --> 00:22:58,126
I think it was around '99.

320
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:04,508
I just happened to be coming out
of the bathhouse after a bath

321
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:07,260
when a very familiar face

322
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:10,597
caught my eye.

323
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:15,060
I walked toward him slowly
to get a better look…

324
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:18,897
and it was Park In-geun.

325
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,525
"That son of a bitch is alive?"

326
00:23:22,818 --> 00:23:26,488
I got goosebumps all over at that moment.

327
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:30,409
I said to myself,
"Isn't that motherfucker Park In-geun?"

328
00:23:31,118 --> 00:23:33,662
I opened my trunk,
grabbed the baseball bat…

329
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:38,250
and yelled,
"You son of a bitch! Park In-geun!"

330
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,001
as I ran toward him.

331
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:44,047
The bastard freaked out
as soon as he saw me,

332
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:48,176
got into his Volvo, and locked the doors.

333
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:51,179
I started hitting the car with the bat

334
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:54,141
while shouting,
"Open the door, you son of a bitch!"

335
00:23:57,227 --> 00:24:00,313
But he was already in the car,
so he took off.

336
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,445
I thought, "I need to kill him."

337
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:08,738
"I'm going to kill that guy."

338
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:11,950
I thought he'd been sentenced
to life in prison.

339
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:14,077
I thought he'd be there for good.

340
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:19,458
He was sentenced to just two years
and six months in prison.

341
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:25,297
No further investigation was conducted

342
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:28,592
into the harm or human rights violations
suffered by the victims.

343
00:24:28,675 --> 00:24:32,262
The investigation only focused

344
00:24:32,345 --> 00:24:35,640
on Park In-geun's corruption
and embezzlement.

345
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:39,811
But they never carried out
a proper investigation.

346
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:44,274
The prosecution openly pressured
investigators to halt the investigation.

347
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:49,738
Despite uncovering nearly 1.1 billion won
in embezzlement by Director Park,

348
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:53,033
there was persistent pressure
to understate the amount.

349
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:55,785
Apparently, he was like an emperor there.

350
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:59,498
In there, he could do whatever he wanted
with the money he had.

351
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:04,669
Even in the detention center,
he still went to bathhouses or cafés.

352
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:07,339
PARK FREQUENTLY LEAVING THE PREMISES
DURING HIS TIME IN DETENTION

353
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:09,883
He was supposed to be behind bars,
but he came and went freely.

354
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,511
A WELFARE FACILITY DIRECTOR
ENJOYS OUTINGS WHILE IN DETENTION

355
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:15,305
Mayor Kim Ju-ho started a campaign
to secure his release.

356
00:25:15,388 --> 00:25:17,307
CHUN DOO-HWAN, PRESIDENT
KIM JU-HO, MAYOR OF BUSAN

357
00:25:17,390 --> 00:25:19,601
He held my hand
and said he didn't want this made public.

358
00:25:20,352 --> 00:25:22,354
I assumed he was someone remarkable.

359
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:25,565
I thought the mayor of Busan
was the most powerful person in Busan.

360
00:25:25,649 --> 00:25:27,275
So this guy was above the mayor.

361
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,489
AFTER 7 TRIALS, PARK GETS
2 YEARS AND 6 MONTHS IN PRISON

362
00:25:32,572 --> 00:25:35,492
FOR EMBEZZLEMENT
AND FOREIGN EXCHANGE VIOLATIONS

363
00:25:44,584 --> 00:25:50,257
Park In-geun, the director, died in 2016.

364
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:53,677
He died in a nursing home.

365
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,805
Back then, I thought,

366
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:58,682
"Couldn't he

367
00:25:59,599 --> 00:26:01,017
at least have apologized

368
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:04,187
before he died?"

369
00:26:04,271 --> 00:26:07,190
"That's the least you could do,
you piece of shit."

370
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:12,737
I'd have rather been the one

371
00:26:14,447 --> 00:26:17,242
to kill Park In-geun back then.

372
00:26:18,034 --> 00:26:20,745
I was in my mid-twenties then,

373
00:26:21,288 --> 00:26:23,248
so I'd have been released by now.

374
00:26:26,835 --> 00:26:33,258
A monster like him was going around
spending money like water.

375
00:26:35,594 --> 00:26:39,931
AFTER HIS RELEASE, PARK IN-GEUN RAN
VARIOUS FOR-PROFIT AND WELFARE BUSINESSES

376
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:42,892
I heard that until the day he died,
he said,

377
00:26:43,685 --> 00:26:45,687
"I did nothing wrong."

378
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:47,814
NEWSTAPA
MARCH 6, 2013

379
00:26:47,897 --> 00:26:50,817
Hello. Are you Director Park In-geun?

380
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:52,110
Who are you with?

381
00:26:52,193 --> 00:26:55,447
-I'm with Newstapa.
-Don't you see him right now?

382
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:59,117
Hey, what if he goes into shock
because of you, huh?

383
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,035
PARK IN-GEUN'S SON

384
00:27:00,118 --> 00:27:01,494
What if he goes into shock?

385
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:04,039
You gonna take responsibility
if he collapses?

386
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:07,125
What have I ever done wrong, huh?

387
00:27:07,208 --> 00:27:10,337
It's been over 20 years, you bastard.
Call your supervisor now.

388
00:27:11,046 --> 00:27:14,215
Hey, tell me something.
Doesn't my father have any rights?

389
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:17,302
Doesn't he have any basic human rights?

390
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:19,929
Tell me. Does he not have any rights?

391
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:22,265
Please calm down.

392
00:27:24,017 --> 00:27:26,311
JO SEONG-HYEON
DIRECTOR OF THE ECHOES OF SURVIVORS

393
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:29,856
The interview you just saw was
the last time Park In-geun was on tape.

394
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:33,860
Here's one thing we should remember.

395
00:27:33,943 --> 00:27:38,114
From the day he was released
to the day he died,

396
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:43,161
Park In-geun never once apologized
to the Brothers' Home victims.

397
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:47,999
Does his family still think the same way?

398
00:27:52,337 --> 00:27:54,422
We went to great lengths

399
00:27:54,506 --> 00:27:59,094
to finally get hold
of a member of Park In-geun's family.

400
00:28:08,561 --> 00:28:13,566
PARK CHEON-GWANG, PARK'S YOUNGEST SON
CHAIRMAN OF THE BROTHERS' HOME FOUNDATION

401
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:16,653
Are you nervous?

402
00:28:16,736 --> 00:28:18,738
Yes, very much so.

403
00:28:22,325 --> 00:28:25,745
I know it wasn't easy for you
to agree to this interview.

404
00:28:25,829 --> 00:28:27,956
What were you most worried about?

405
00:28:29,290 --> 00:28:32,085
My biggest worry

406
00:28:32,794 --> 00:28:34,462
would be my family.

407
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:37,048
What I worry about most

408
00:28:37,132 --> 00:28:40,844
is the possibility
that my wife and children

409
00:28:40,927 --> 00:28:45,724
might be threatened or put in danger.

410
00:28:46,307 --> 00:28:48,685
Who do you think would harm your family?

411
00:28:49,352 --> 00:28:50,812
The people

412
00:28:51,479 --> 00:28:54,691
who would be upset with me
revealing the truth.

413
00:28:55,358 --> 00:28:57,569
Especially those in the government,

414
00:28:57,652 --> 00:28:58,987
the city of Busan,

415
00:28:59,779 --> 00:29:03,742
and the police.

416
00:29:04,242 --> 00:29:06,953
I don't think
they'd be very happy with this.

417
00:29:09,122 --> 00:29:10,540
Given everything,

418
00:29:10,623 --> 00:29:13,334
what made you decide to do this interview?

419
00:29:15,128 --> 00:29:20,049
The reason I wanted to come
and speak with you

420
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,093
is to tell you

421
00:29:23,678 --> 00:29:27,640
that Director Park In-geun
of Brothers' Home wasn't the only one

422
00:29:28,141 --> 00:29:30,560
responsible for everything that happened.

423
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:35,815
I think my father was about 30% to blame

424
00:29:37,358 --> 00:29:39,819
and the government about 70%.

425
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:42,238
That's what I believe.

426
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:45,033
PARK IN-GEUN

427
00:29:45,116 --> 00:29:47,452
At the time, my father said

428
00:29:47,535 --> 00:29:51,998
it was a direct order from the government,
issued by the president.

429
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:55,210
As far as I know,

430
00:29:55,710 --> 00:29:59,839
President Chun Doo-hwan
even presented my father with a medal

431
00:29:59,923 --> 00:30:01,966
and offered significant support.

432
00:30:03,885 --> 00:30:07,472
Near Hwangnyeongsan Mountain in Busan,

433
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:08,932
there used to be

434
00:30:09,682 --> 00:30:10,725
a presidential villa.

435
00:30:11,017 --> 00:30:12,435
THE VILLA OF PRESIDENT CHUN DOO-HWAN

436
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:13,853
We went all the way there,

437
00:30:14,479 --> 00:30:17,065
and I waited in the car
while my father went inside

438
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:18,817
to speak with the president.

439
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:23,655
He even got a watch from the president.

440
00:30:26,032 --> 00:30:28,284
Once, while he was driving,

441
00:30:28,827 --> 00:30:31,204
he was stopped by the police
for running a red light.

442
00:30:32,705 --> 00:30:37,585
But once they saw the watch
from the president, they just let him go.

443
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:43,383
They gave him a medal
and made him do the work, but later,

444
00:30:43,883 --> 00:30:48,471
when the president found him inconvenient,

445
00:30:48,555 --> 00:30:50,473
he made my father take the fall.

446
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:53,643
Then why give him the medal?

447
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:57,188
It's pretty absurd, isn't it?

448
