Seoul has been chosen
to host the '88 Olympics.

449
00:31:16,082 --> 00:31:19,252
As citizens of the Olympic host nation

450
00:31:19,752 --> 00:31:22,130
and as citizens

451
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:25,967
of a country emerging as a global player,

452
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:29,345
we must earn the trust and respect

453
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:33,057
of people around the world.

454
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:36,144
LET'S PURIFY OUR SURROUNDINGS
TO BUILD A BRIGHTER SOCIETY

455
00:31:36,227 --> 00:31:39,772
After Seoul was confirmed
as the host of the '88 Olympics,

456
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,941
there was a push to clean up the streets.

457
00:31:42,567 --> 00:31:47,947
To show foreigners that Korea
is a clean and developed country.

458
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:51,993
The poor, beggars, and street gum vendors.

459
00:31:52,076 --> 00:31:55,747
They didn't want people like that
to be seen.

460
00:31:55,830 --> 00:31:57,540
MINISTRY OF HOME AFFAIRS DIRECTIVE NO. 410

461
00:31:57,624 --> 00:32:00,126
They carried out a crackdown on vagrants

462
00:32:00,209 --> 00:32:04,130
under Directive No. 410,
issued by the Ministry of Home Affairs.

463
00:32:04,213 --> 00:32:05,590
DEFINITION OF A VAGRANT

464
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:11,012
I see it as a kind of human cleanup,
meant to remove citizens,

465
00:32:11,095 --> 00:32:16,768
including the innocent and vulnerable,
from the streets.

466
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:20,939
Back then,

467
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:24,567
everyone loved Director Park In-geun.

468
00:32:24,651 --> 00:32:26,069
VAGRANTS BEING SENT TO BROTHERS' HOME

469
00:32:26,152 --> 00:32:29,364
Just one call was enough
to take care of them.

470
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:32,492
The program was a major success
in Busan at the time.

471
00:32:33,618 --> 00:32:35,912
No other country
does it better than we do.

472
00:32:35,995 --> 00:32:40,083
There's not a single beggar
on the streets.

473
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,128
Do you see any beggars in Korea?
Take a look. We have none.

474
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:48,424
There's an uproar over a single death
at the facility in Busan,

475
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:53,471
but in a developed country like the US,
that's barely an issue.

476
00:32:54,138 --> 00:32:55,306
Not even an issue.

477
00:32:55,807 --> 00:33:00,353
They found the record books documenting

478
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:04,357
when the police handed people over
to Brothers' Home.

479
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:09,570
The names of police officers,
civil servants,

480
00:33:09,654 --> 00:33:12,240
and those who were captured were on them.

481
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:13,449
BROTHERS' HOME INTAKE FORM

482
00:33:13,533 --> 00:33:17,537
They recorded when, where,
and how those people were captured.

483
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:23,835
Nearly 80% of them
were taken in by the police.

