the people I hate most are the police.

489
00:33:43,062 --> 00:33:44,272
I want to kill him.

490
00:33:45,815 --> 00:33:48,109
How could a police officer say
they'd take me home,

491
00:33:48,192 --> 00:33:52,405
then take me to Brothers' Home instead?

492
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:56,034
I want to see his face one more time

493
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:58,411
if he's still alive.

494
00:34:05,001 --> 00:34:07,128
MOON JEONG-SU, FORMER ASSEMBLY MEMBER
NEW KOREA DEMOCRATIC PARTY

495
00:34:07,211 --> 00:34:09,422
Bringing an ordinary public order offender
to the station

496
00:34:09,505 --> 00:34:12,967
only added a mere two points
to an officer's performance score.

497
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:18,723
However, turning in a beggar or vagrant
to the Brothers' Home…

498
00:34:18,806 --> 00:34:19,724
PERFORMANCE SCORE

499
00:34:19,807 --> 00:34:21,476
…earned them five points.

500
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:24,896
DETAINMENT, 2-3 POINTS
ADMISSION TO BROTHERS' HOME, 5 POINTS

501
00:34:24,979 --> 00:34:27,857
One of the things
that motivated the police officers

502
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:31,235
to be more vigilant and active

503
00:34:32,528 --> 00:34:35,406
was the bribes they received.

504
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:40,411
Whenever officers handed people over
to Brothers' Home,

505
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:44,040
the staff there slipped them some money.

506
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:53,341
At the time, police officers
frequently visited my father's office.

507
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:58,387
He sometimes handed them cash.

508
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:05,311
There was this team leader
at the Geumjeong police station.

509
00:35:05,394 --> 00:35:08,648
I think my father gave him
around five million won as well.

510
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:11,901
Put simply, it was a bribe.

511
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:15,655
Were there any officers
who refused to take bribes?

512
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:18,533
I don't think I've seen any.

513
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:23,037
WHO IS BROTHERS' HOME DIRECTOR PARK,
A MEDALED MEMBER OF THE PUAC?

514
00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:25,998
DIRECTOR OF BROTHERS' HOME
EMBEZZLES 1.1 BILLION WON

515
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:30,002
WHY HASN'T THE BROTHERS' HOME CORRUPTION
BEEN BROUGHT TO LIGHT?

516
00:35:32,421 --> 00:35:35,216
What happened to your family
after your father was arrested

517
00:35:35,299 --> 00:35:37,677
and Brothers' Home was closed?

518
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:46,853
After his release
following his arrest in '86,

519
00:35:46,936 --> 00:35:51,149
my father decided
that we would immigrate to Australia

520
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:54,110
in 1990.

521
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:58,406
Our family's total assets

522
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:01,617
were once appraised at 36 billion won.

523
00:36:01,701 --> 00:36:03,870
That was in 2011.

524
00:36:06,164 --> 00:36:11,335
We owned a property in Australia
called the Milperra Sports Centre.

525
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:19,343
In Australia, they currently hold assets
worth about 14 billion won.

526
00:36:20,469 --> 00:36:22,847
I believe his third daughter
and her husband

527
00:36:22,930 --> 00:36:27,059
currently own the golf course
and sports center.

528
00:36:27,143 --> 00:36:29,979
PARK'S THIRD DAUGHTER AND HER HUSBAND
CURRENT OWNERS OF THE GOLF COURSE

529
00:36:31,939 --> 00:36:35,359
After planning our immigration
to Australia,

530
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:37,028
my father secured the funds…

531
00:36:37,111 --> 00:36:39,780
EMPLOYEE OF VAGRANT FACILITY
IN WASHINGTON, UNITED STATES

532
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:42,658
…to buy the business in Milperra.

533
00:36:42,742 --> 00:36:45,286
Even when Min Gyeong-u,
my third brother-in-law, ran it…

534
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:47,371
AUSTRALIA BUSINESS REPORTS
BROTHERS' HOME FOUNDATION

535
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:50,791
…he used to give my father daily updates
on revenue and expenses.

536
00:36:52,501 --> 00:36:56,964
It clearly shows
that my father was the real owner.

537
00:36:58,758 --> 00:37:01,093
The assets he siphoned off to Australia

538
00:37:01,844 --> 00:37:04,096
were the assets of Brothers' Home.

539
00:37:04,180 --> 00:37:06,515
To put it simply,
it's the proceeds of crime.

540
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:09,060
"This is what I inherited from my father."

541
